{"type":"message","id":"116bc765","parentId":"ac25fd46","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:00:48.918Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0yacok3vgmlw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Recipes\n\nStore your recipes here!\n\n## Categories\n\n- Breakfast\n- Lunch\n- Dinner\n- Snacks\n- Desserts\n- Drinks\n\n## Notes\n\nAdd your favorite recipes with ingredients and instructions.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774764048918}}
{"type":"message","id":"c2b1b1d9","parentId":"116bc765","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:00:48.919Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0yacok3vgmlw_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Giant Meatballs Baked in Tomato Sauce\n\n**Source:** Simply Whisked\n**Rating:** 4.67/5 (15 votes)\n**Time:** 1 hr 5 mins (Prep: 15 min, Cook: 50 min)\n**Servings:** 20 meatballs\n\n---\n\n## Description\nOutshine ordinary meatballs and go big with these extraordinary, giant meatballs baked in tomato sauce. These hearty and robust meatballs are larger than life and packed with incredible flavors. Smothered in a classic Italian tomato sauce, these meatballs can be served with or without your favorite pasta.\n\n---\n\n## Ingredients\n\n### For the Meatballs\n- ⚠️ **IMPORTANT: Use PANKO breadcrumbs (Italian-style), NOT regular Italian breadcrumbs!**\n- 3 pounds ground turkey\n- 1 cup Italian-style Panko breadcrumbs\n- 2 large eggs\n- 2 tablespoons dried basil\n- 1 tablespoon dried parsley\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 2 teaspoons coarse salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n### For the Sauce\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large garlic clove (minced)\n- 1/8 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes\n- 2 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 1 28-ounce can crushed tomatoes\n- 1 1/2 teaspoons dried basil\n- 1 teaspoon dried parsley\n- 1/4 teaspoon coarse salt\n- 1/8 teaspoon pepper\n\n---\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Make the sauce:** In a large saucepan, heat olive oil, garlic and crushed red pepper flakes over medium heat until sizzling. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat and keep warm.\n\n2. **Make the meatballs:** Preheat oven to 375°F. In a large bowl, mix meatball ingredients until evenly combined. Portion meatball mixture into 1/4 pound pieces, rolling into balls.\n\n3. **Bake first round:** Place meatballs in a large baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes.\n\n4. **Add sauce and bake again:** Remove dish from oven and top meatballs with about half of the sauce mixture. Return to oven and bake for an additional 25-30 minutes, or until meatballs have reached an internal temperature of 165°F.\n\n5. **Serve:** Top with remaining sauce and serve.\n\n---\n\n## Nutrition\n- Calories: 160kcal\n- Carbohydrates: 5g\n- Protein: 15g\n- Fat: 8g\n- Cholesterol: 61mg\n- Sodium: 453mg\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774764048919}}
{"type":"message","id":"02f4163f","parentId":"c2b1b1d9","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:00:56.159Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the recipe folder with some delicious-sounding recipes. Currently there's just one recipe: Giant Meatballs Baked in Tomato Sauce. There's also a README that mentions categories like Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, Snacks, Desserts, and Drinks - so it seems like the folder is set up for more recipes to be added.\n\nLet me let Bobby know I found it and what I see!","thinkingSignature":"aa307c5d77f97e6a2523d2b2d2fbea3d5f024ef262c59616c12e9109079711a8"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\nFound it! 🎉 Your Recipes folder on the Desktop has:\n\n- **Giant Meatballs Baked in Tomato Sauce** — Simply Whisked recipe, 4.67/5 stars, feeds about 20 meatballs\n\nThe folder's README mentions categories set up for Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, Snacks, Desserts, and Drinks — so it's ready for more recipes!\n\nYou can add more recipes there and I'll always check the folder when you ask about cooking or baking. Want me to help you make those giant meatballs sometime? 🍝\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1593,"output":198,"cacheRead":18571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20362,"cost":{"input":0.00047789999999999996,"output":0.0002376,"cacheRead":0.00111426,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00182976}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774764048919,"responseId":"0617f311202cd6bfa0c1ddd9ad917655"}}
