{"type":"message","id":"e87b0a07","parentId":"77115325","timestamp":"2026-04-06T19:27:33.839Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is telling me not to put \"final\" at the end of my messages. He's right - that's a formatting thing from the system that I shouldn't include in my actual replies. I'll just respond naturally without that tag.","thinkingSignature":"1132f12e827e23f0a7011b985240223376a08089d1846efadfd289579b335425"},{"type":"text","text":"Oh my bad! Got it, Bobby. I'll just reply normally from now on. 😄"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80,"output":67,"cacheRead":35139,"cacheWrite":234,"totalTokens":35520,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775503651065,"responseId":"06233c23a5785e080e49b6a0fda0bd09"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c06b40fb","parentId":"e87b0a07","timestamp":"2026-04-06T19:33:46.406Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-04-06 15:32 EDT] I’m doing 5 large eggs. What’s the nutrition on that?"}],"timestamp":1775504026406,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:main:main","sourceTool":"sessions_send"}}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e703f47","parentId":"c06b40fb","timestamp":"2026-04-06T19:33:54.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to know the nutrition for 5 large eggs. Let me calculate that based on standard nutritional info for large eggs.","thinkingSignature":"cfbaef2b22b356f3cb9ba09f41c0f39d8c083ce37e4394d5b9c3cce7e6b9605b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n5 large eggs comes out to about:\n\n| | Amount |\n|---|---|\n| **Calories** | ~360–375 cal |\n| **Protein** | ~30–32g |\n| **Fat** | ~24–25g |\n| **Cholesterol** | ~1,065mg |\n| **Carbs** | ~2g (basically none) |\n\n**A few quick notes:**\n\n- That's a solid **high-protein, low-carb** meal — great if you're active or watching carbs\n- The fat is mostly in the yolks, which also means you get all the **vitamin D, choline, and B12**\n- If you're watching cholesterol, that 1,065mg is worth noting (daily limit is typically 300mg for some people), but for most healthy folks it's totally fine\n\nSo 5 eggs is a pretty hearty meal — definitely on the bigger side. You might scale back to 3–4 if you're not super hungry or active that day. 🍳\n\nWhat are you making — scrambled, fried, boiled? I can help with that too! 🍪👨‍🍳"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80,"output":256,"cacheRead":8792,"cacheWrite":26657,"totalTokens":35785,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775504026407,"responseId":"06233d9af713e494bd1c6440e6a4e8d6"}}
